# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# AI Content Service — Environment Configuration
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Setup instructions:
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Fill in your API keys (see below)
# 3. Restart service: npm run dev
#
# For detailed setup guide, see README.md → Environment Setup
#

# ── Anthropic AI (REQUIRED for content generation) ─────────
#
# Get your key at: https://console.anthropic.com/
# - Create account or log in
# - Navigate to "API Keys"
# - Click "Create Key"
# - Copy key starting with sk-ant-api03-...
#
# Without this key:
# - /generate/round returns 503 Service Unavailable
# - /generate/destination returns 503
# - You can still use pre-generated content packs
#
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-api03-your-key-here


# ── ElevenLabs TTS (Optional for voice synthesis) ──────────
#
# Get your key at: https://elevenlabs.io/
# - Create account
# - Go to Profile → API Keys
# - Copy your API key
#
# Without this key:
# - TTS runs in MOCK MODE (generates silent WAV files)
# - Useful for development/testing without voice
#
# Leave blank or comment out for mock mode:
# ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=
#
ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=sk-your-elevenlabs-key-here

# Default voice for TTS (Rachel)
# Find more voices at: https://elevenlabs.io/voice-library
ELEVENLABS_DEFAULT_VOICE_ID=21m00Tcbv0mMvdtTrqFLmxvi


# ── TTS Cache ───────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Directory for caching generated audio clips
# Prevents regenerating identical phrases
#
TTS_CACHE_DIR=/tmp/pa-sparet-tts-cache


# ── Service Configuration ───────────────────────────────────
#
# Port for the service
PORT=3001

# Public base URL for TTS audio file URLs
# For local development: http://localhost:3001
# For tvOS access: Set to your machine's LAN IP (e.g., http://192.168.1.100:3001)
PUBLIC_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3001
